    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-06-10T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-06-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="76"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/6–1052: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DJC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-06-10T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 10, 1952—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7701. Rptd info Saigon 439, London unn. <persName corresp="#p_LJ2"
                        >Letourneau</persName> made fol comments to <persName corresp="#p_ATC1"
                        >Achilles</persName> during luncheon yesterday: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>He hopes tripartite <gloss target="#t_POL1">pol</gloss> talks can be
                            held when the Secy returns Eur in late June, either in London or
                            Paris.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>He suggests some continuing tripartite body, presumably informal, to
                            discuss <gloss target="#t_POL1">pol</gloss> aspects <gloss
                                target="#t_IC1">IC</gloss>.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>He suggests establishment some form of tripartite mil body on <gloss
                                target="#t_IC1">IC</gloss>, perhaps in Honolulu, Singapore, Saigon
                            or one of three capitals.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Since neither Fr nor US “cld send another man” to fight on ground in
                                <gloss target="#t_IC1">IC</gloss>, he wonders whether Australia cld
                            not be persuaded send troops.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Sitn has improved materially during past year, both psychologically
                            and militarily. “A year ago Viet were afraid we wld stay; now they are
                            afraid we will go.”</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>In reply to comment that much thinking seemed to be in negative terms
                            of holding on in <gloss target="#t_IC1">IC</gloss> rather than of
                            winning war, we [<hi rend="italic">he</hi>] replied without any
                            elaboration, “best we can hope for is to hold on until general internal
                            sitn has improved sufficiently for us to negot settlement.”</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> comment:</hi> While <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJ2">Letourneau</persName> did not elaborate on point in para
                    nbr 6, presumably he had in mind possibility inclusion <gloss target="#t_IC1"
                        >IC</gloss> in any <pb facs="0212" n="180" xml:id="pg_180"/> overall <gloss
                        target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss> settlement. We believe this question and general
                    question possibility negots <persName corresp="#p_HCM1">Ho Chi-Minh</persName>
                    shld be discussed with <persName corresp="#p_LJ2">Letourneau</persName> in Wash
                    talks with view obtaining definite expose Fr attitude re this problem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dunn</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
